{"id":1320413834,"question_id":3501,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"4 days, 13 hours","timestamp":1720933955,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"702 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1320413834/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Delete Nodes From Linked List Present in Array","memory":"54.8 MB","code":"# Definition for singly-linked list.\n# class ListNode:\n#     def __init__(self, val=0, next=None):\n#         self.val = val\n#         self.next = next\nclass Solution:\n    def modifiedList(self, nums: List[int], head: Optional[ListNode]) -> Optional[ListNode]:\n        rem = set(nums)\n\n        while head and head.val in rem:\n            head = head.next\n        \n        curr = head\n        while curr and curr.next:\n            if curr.next.val in rem:\n                curr.next = curr.next.next\n            else:\n                curr = curr.next\n\n        return head\n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"delete-nodes-from-linked-list-present-in-array","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
